  <front>
   <head>SONNET [57] LVII. To Dependence.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">DEPENDENCE! heavy, heavy are thy chains,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And happier they, who from the dangerous sea,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Or the dark mine, procure with ceaseless pains</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">A hard earn'd pittance — than who trust to thee!</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">More blest the hind, who, from his bed of flock</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Starts! when the birds of morn their summons give,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And waken'd by the lark, 'the sheperd's clock',</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Lives but to labour — labouring but to live.</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">More noble than the sycophant, whose art</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Must heap with taudry flow'rs thy hated shrine;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">I envy not the meed thou canst impart</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To crown  service — while, tho' Pride combine</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">With Fraud to crush me — my unfetter'd heart</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Still to the Mountain Nymph may offer mine.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
